Prospect was first listed as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]].<ref name=2010CensusLA>{{Cite web|title= 2010 Census of Population - Population and Housing Unit Counts - Louisiana |url=https://www2.census.gov/library/publications/decennial/2010/cph-2/cph-2-20.pdf|website=[[United States Census Bureau]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240402175429/https://www2.census.gov/library/publications/decennial/2010/cph-2/cph-2-20.pdf| archive-date=April 2, 2024}}</ref>

As of the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]], there were 476 people with 170 households, for a population density of 323/sq mi. The racial makeup of the community was 0.63% [[African American (U.S. Census)|Black]] or [[Race (United States Census)|African American]], 95.38% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.63% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.42% Asian, and 2.94% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]].  1.63% of the population were [[Hispanics in the United States|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race. 50% of the population are male thus the other 50% are female.

The median age of Prospect was 34.6 which is lower than the US median, 37.3. 52.69% of the population are married, 13.26% are divorced. The average household size is 2.79 people. 34.65% of people who have children are married couples while 14.96% who have children are single.

The median home cost was $93,600 with a cost of living at 14.90% and the unemployment rate was 8.60%.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.bestplaces.net/city/louisiana/prospect | title = Interesting Facts about Prospect, Louisiana | accessdate = 2013-03-08}}</ref>

